notes: This map illustrates satellite-detected, potential damaged structures in Bahia de Caraquez, Manabi Province, Ecuador. The analyzed area is located approximately 120 km south of the 16 April 2016 Muisne earthquake mainshock epicenter. This analysis is done using Pléiades satellite image acquired 19 April 2016 and a WorldView-2 image acquired 02 December 2013. UNITAR-UNOSAT identified 122 potentially damaged structures of which 30 are destroyed, 34 severely damaged, and 62 moderately damaged. This is a preliminary analysis and not yet been validated in the field. Please send ground feedback to UNITAR-UNOSAT.
